laboratory_examinations.findings: Tumor at the gastric fornix near the gastric cardia measuring 11.4 Ã— 12.4 mm. No cystic or calcified components identified.
Shadow defect in the gastric fornix, dull angle of His, and severe gastroesophageal reflux. Aspiration of regurgitated contrast resulted in an extensive bronchogram.
Tumorous lesion measuring 11 mm in diameter at the fornix.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Histological examination of excised gastric polypoid lesion
laboratory_examinations.findings: Epithelium composed of multilayered columnar epithelium and multilayered squamous epithelium. Subepithelial stroma was edematous with structures resembling bronchial glands. A layer of cartilage formed an inverted U-shape.
